# Meal generation (server-side only). Copy to `.env` locally — never commit `.env`.
#
# Real generation (pick one):
# - Claude (Anthropic): ANTHROPIC_API_KEY
# - Gemini (Google AI Studio): GEMINI_API_KEY
# - Groq (OpenAI-compatible): GROQ_API_KEY
#
# If ANTHROPIC_API_KEY, GEMINI_API_KEY, or GROQ_API_KEY is set, that provider is used automatically.
#
# Optional models:
# - ANTHROPIC_MODEL (default: claude-sonnet-4-20250514)
# - GEMINI_MODEL (default: gemini-2.5-flash)
# - GEMINI_MAX_RETRIES (default: 5) — retries with backoff on 503 / overload / rate limits
# - GROQ_MODEL (default: llama-3.1-70b-versatile)
#
# Offline / sample recipes when you have NO API keys:
# - MOCK_GENERATION=1
#
# Force sample recipes even when keys exist (dev only):
# - FORCE_MOCK=1
#
# Troubleshooting “API_KEY_INVALID”:
# - Run `npm run check-gemini` in this folder. If that fails, fix the key or enable
#   “Generative Language API” in Google Cloud for the key’s project; set key restrictions
#   to “None” for local/server calls (HTTP referrer rules break Node).
# - If `check-gemini` passes but the app fails: restart `npm run dev` and ensure you did
#   not `export GEMINI_API_KEY=...` in the shell with an old value (use `.env` only).
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
ANTHROPIC_MODEL=
GEMINI_API_KEY=
GEMINI_MODEL=
GROQ_API_KEY=
GROQ_MODEL=
# MOCK_GENERATION=1
# FORCE_MOCK=1
